or.%3Cp%3EGretchen%20Kay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20bought%20their%20brand%20new%20condo%20on%20the%20beach%20for%20%24115%2C000%20in%20Ecuador%20and%20said%20similar%20condos%20rent%20for%20%24800%20monthly.%20She%20said%20the%20prices%20have%20stayed%20rather%20low%20because%20of%20a%20huge%20earthquake%20in%202016%20that%20damaged%20many%20properties%20along%20the%20coast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGretchen%20said%20her%20HOA%20fee%20%E2%80%94%20which%20includes%20property%20insurance%20%E2%80%94%20is%20%24160%20a%20month%2C%20her%20electricity%20is%20about%20%24100%20monthly%2C%20and%20property%20taxes%20are%20%2460%20yearly.%20In%20Utah%2C%20they%20paid%20over%20%241%2C000%20a%20year%20in%20property%20insurance%20and%20about%20%241%2C000%20in%20property%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20hardly%20any%20cost%20of%20living%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Gretchen%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20groceries%20are%20the%20only%20expense%20similar%20to%20the%20US%20due%20to%20tariffs%20on%20many%20imported%20goods.%20Still%2C%20eating%20out%20is%20often%20about%20a%20third%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20similar%20meal%20in%20the%20US.%20They%20decided%20not%20to%20have%20a%20car%20given%20frequent%20buses%20and%20inexpensive%20taxis%2C%20which%20are%20about%20%248%20to%20the%20grocery%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-savings-medical-costs-baby-boomers-paying-for-cancer-treatment-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedical%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20much%20lower%20in%20Ecuador.%20After%20a%20hip%20replacement%20she%20received%20in%20the%20US%20failed%2C%20she%20was%20rushed%20to%20the%20hospital%20in%20Ecuador%20and%20paid%20%246%2C000%20for%20the%20surgery.%20When%20she%20asked%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%20how%20much%20that%20surgery%20would%20have%20cost%20in%20the%20US%2C%20she%20was%20told%20%2480%2C000.%20Whereas%20she%20said%20an%20MRI%20in%20Ecuador%20is%20%24190%2C%20it's%20over%20%241%2C000%20in%20the%20US.%20She%20also%20said%20she's%20taken%20care%20of%20immediately%20and%20can%20easily%20secure%20medical%20appointments%2C%20while%20she%20often%20waited%20months%20to%20get%20a%20similar%20appointment%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cacti%20in%20the%20Galapagos%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb2f07ce3009a0fac766cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGretchen%20Kay%20and%20her%20husband%20have%20taken%20trips%20to%20the%20Galapagos%20Islands%20nearby.%3Cp%3EGretchen%20Kay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20Medicare%2C%20with%20all%20the%20supplements%20that%20you%20need%20and%20the%20different%20parts%2C%20was%20way%20over%20our%20financial%20ability%2C%20and%20you%20still%20have%20to%20pay%2020%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Gretchen%20said.%20%26quot%3BHere%2C%20we%20could%20get%20on%20the%20national%20health%20plan%20for%20%2480%20a%20month%20for%20both%20of%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20some%20time%20to%20get%20adjusted%20to%20Ecuador's%20emphasis%20on%20independence%20and%20%26quot%3Bpersonal%20responsibility.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20many%20homes%20are%20surrounded%20by%20barbed%20wire%2C%20while%20her%20complex%20has%20four%20security%20doors.%20She%20added%20that%20police%20often%20won't%20respond%20to%20smaller%20incidents%2C%20and%20the%20infrastructure%20is%20often%20%26quot%3Bchaotic%26quot%3B%20and%20hard%20to%20navigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2213f57b5b-0f4f-4e86-989f-50f95e902e29%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELife%20is%20sometimes%20lonely%20and%20monotonous%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThey've%20taken%20some%20trips%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20including%20Quito%2C%20Cuenca%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-on-the-galpagos-islands-according-to-frequent-visitor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGalapagos%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20Gretchen%20said%20they%20have%20little%20desire%20to%20continue%20exploring%20as%20the%20roads%20are%20often%20difficult%20to%20navigate%2C%20and%20they're%20content%20with%20spending%20their%20time%20in%20their%20small%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20much%20more%20lively%20social%20group%20here%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20and%20they%20had%20cars%2C%20so%20we%20would%20go%20the%20nearest%20little%20town%20for%20karaoke%20or%20trivia%20nights%2C%26quot%3B%20Gretchen%20said.%20%26quot%3BThen%2C%20those%20people%20moved%20away%20or%20died%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20decided%20it%20wasn't%20worth%20it%20for%20us%20to%20keep%20taking%20taxis%20into%20town.%20We%20don't%20really%20go%20unless%20someone%20else%20invites%20us%2C%20and%20that's%20kind%20of%20a%20shame.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20her%20age%2C%20she%20said%20she's%20lost%20some%20of%20the%20energy%20to%20explore%20and%20get%20acquainted%20with%20the%20locals%20in%20her%20area%2C%20though%20she%20said%20she%20regrets%20not%20putting%20in%20more%20effort.%20She%20said%20many%20locals%20are%20welcoming%20and%20appreciative%20that%20many%20expats%20are%20respectful%20of%20their%20heritage%20and%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20really%20polite%20and%20careful%20and%20deferential%20to%20the%20locals%3B%20we%20never%20act%20like%20loud%20Americans%2C%26quot%3B%20Gretchen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20has%20plenty%20of%20hobbies%20she%20wanted%20to%20start%20in%20Ecuador%2C%20though%20her%20hip%20problems%20and%20skin%20cancer%20put%20a%20wrench%20in%20her%20plans.%20She's%20trying%20to%20find%20more%20sedentary%20hobbies%20such%20as%20cooking%20or%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20kind%20of%20embarrassed%20to%20admit%20we're%20in%20the%20category%20of%20never%20leaving%20the%20complex%3B%20we%20found%20a%20gringo%20complex%20here%2C%20and%20we%20pretty%20much%20just%20stay%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Gretchen%20said.%20%26quot%3BOur%20only%20interactions%20are%20at%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20our%20taxi%20drivers%2C%20and%20repair%20people%2C%20and%20for%20that%2C%20we%20use%20Google%20Translate.%20We%20thought%20we%20would%20learn%20Spanish%20by%20osmosis%2C%20but%20we%20haven't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20recently%20left%20the%20United%20States%20for%20a%20new%20country%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ansheidlower%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ensheidlower%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-couldnt-afford-retirement-moved-ecuador-cheaper-lonely-social-security-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726825742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eb2d59d17aa3c7b2b3e8db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-couldnt-afford-retirement-moved-ecuador-cheaper-lonely-social-security-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gretchen%20and%20her%20husband%20Robert%20moved%20to%20Ecuador%20to%20afford%20retirement%20and%20said%20healthcare%20and%20housing%20costs%20are%20much%20cheaper%20than%20in%20the%20US.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-couldnt-afford-retirement-moved-ecuador-cheaper-lonely-social-security-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Mommy%20brain%20explained%3A%20How%20the%20brain%20restructures%20after%20pregnancy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726825646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113521856%2Cimgsize-4023156.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofin