st%20every%20parent%20struggles%20with%20when%20their%20children%20are%20young.%20I%20know%20that%20sometimes%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwife-made-six-figures-husband-stayed-home-with-kids-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eone%20parent%20can%20stay%20home%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20their%20children%20until%20they%20are%20school-age%2C%20but%20in%20my%20situation%2C%20that%20wasn't%20going%20to%20be%20possible.%20I%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20feelings%20about%20not%20being%20able%20to%20be%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%2C%20but%20I%20also%20didn't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20to%20dwell%20on%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20I%20knew%20I%20would%20have%20to%20earn%20an%20income%2C%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20be%20present%20for%20that%20part%20of%20my%20son's%20life%20when%20he%20was%20little%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20that%20spending%20time%20with%20an%20attentive%20parent%20was%20important%20for%20his%20development.%20But%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-parent-loneliness-no-partner-202404%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20a%20single%20mom%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20without%20much%20willing%20help%20from%20family%20members%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20get%20creative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222f3af9f3-8c76-478a-9d00-d2eca388a9b8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20worked%20part-time%20jobs%20that%20let%20me%20make%20my%20own%20schedule%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20able%20to%20take%20care%20of%20my%20son%20and%20me%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingle-mom-running-business-tips-work-life-balance-find-time-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehaving%20a%20small%20business%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20being%20an%20independent%20contractor.%20I%20cleaned%20homes%20for%20a%20small%20number%20of%20clients%20and%20taught%20yoga%20classes%20in%20the%20community%20throughout%20the%20week.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECleaning%20someone's%20home%20for%20three%20to%20five%20hours%20could%20earn%20me%20between%20%2475%20and%20%24150.%20Depending%20on%20which%20yoga%20studio%20I%20was%20teaching%20at%20and%20how%20many%20students%20attended%2C%20I%20made%20between%20%2420%20and%20%24100%20per%20one-hour%20class.%20The%20best%20part%20about%20being%20my%20own%20boss%2C%20though%2C%20was%20having%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20my%20own%20schedule%2C%20including%20rescheduling%20if%20my%20son%20got%20sick.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227a345b3a-cda6-4f4c-993e-c9befdea092d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20found%20a%20morning-only%20preschool%20program%20for%20my%20son%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThrough%20other%20moms%2C%20I%20heard%20about%20a%20church%20not%20very%20far%20from%20where%20we%20were%20living%20that%20offered%20schooling%20in%20the%20mornings.%20Not%20only%20had%20it%20come%20highly%20recommended%20by%20other%20mothers%2C%20but%20it%20was%20affordable.%20After%20a%20visit%20and%20talk%20with%20the%20school's%20director%2C%20I%20enrolled%20my%20son.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20less%20than%20%24250%20a%20month%2C%20my%20son%20could%20be%20in%20school%20for%20up%20to%20six%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20from%208%20a.m.%20to%202%20p.m.%20I%20didn't%20worry%20about%20him%20while%20he%20was%20there%20or%20feel%20guilty%20about%20it%20because%20I%20knew%20he%20was%20getting%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildcare-is-unaffordable-almost-everywhere-in-america-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egood%20early%20education%20and%20socialization%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20arranged%20my%20schedule%20so%20that%20I%20only%20worked%20when%20my%20son%20was%20in%20school%20or%20with%20his%20dad%20for%20part%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch