%20to%20work%20as%20hard%20as%20I%20did%20to%20earn%20enough%20money%20and%20still%20find%20a%20way%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-life-balance-financial-goals-raising-son-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebe%20present%20with%20my%20son%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I%20was%20lucky%20that%20I%20was%20young%20at%20the%20time%20and%20still%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20energy.%20But%20thinking%20back%20to%20that%20time%20period%20today%2C%20I%20do%20remember%20being%20bone-tired.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20I%20only%20found%20a%20way%20to%20achieve%20the%20work-life%20balance%20I%20felt%20my%20son%20needed%20and%20that%20I%20wanted%20out%20of%20sheer%20survival.%20Not%20wanting%20to%20have%20to%20work%20full-time%20when%20my%20son%20was%20that%20little%20was%20the%20main%20driver%20behind%20all%20of%20those%20decisions%20early%20in%20his%20life%20and%20my%20journey%20as%20a%20new%20mom.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favoiding-daycare-single-mom-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726825082000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eaccfdd17aa3c7b2b3a54a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favoiding-daycare-single-mom-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20single%20mom%20managed%20to%20avoid%20paying%20for%20day%20care.%20She%20found%20jobs%20that%20let%20her%20create%20my%20own%20schedule%20and%20went%20to%20school%20at%20night.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ashley%20Archambault)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Favoiding-daycare-single-mom-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20The%20Changing%20Nature%20Of%20Poverty%20In%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fw.ndtvimg.com%2Fsites%2F3%2F2021%2F01%2F24194128%2F660x330-hunger.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoverty%20has%20long%20been%20a%20subject%20of%20debate.%20Growth%20generally%20reduces%20poverty%2C%20but%20its%20composition%20matters%2C%20too.%20Poverty%20is%20commonly%20measured%20through%20headcount%20ratios%2C%20which%20reflect%20the%20percentage%20of%20the%20population%20below%20a%20defined%20poverty%20line%20based%20on%20the%20minimum%20basket%20of%20goods%20and%20services%20required%20for%20subsistence.%20In%20India%2C%20this%20method%2C%20established%20in%20the%201950s%20and%20refined%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20uses%20monthly%20per%20capita%20consumption%20expenditure%20to%20determine%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20as%20income%20data%20from%20household%20surveys%20are%20unreliable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeasuring%20poverty%20requires%20both%20a%20poverty%20line%20and%20accurate%20data%2C%20with%20the%20Household%20Consumption%20Expenditure%20Survey%20forming%20the%20basis%20for%20poverty%20estimation.%20This%20detailed%20survey%20covers%20expenditure%20on%20around%20350%20items%2C%20including%20food%2C%20clothing%2C%20education%2C%20and%20health.%20However%2C%20until%20recently%2C%20the%20latest%20available%20results%20are%20from%202011-12.%20While%20attempts%20to%20create%20multidimensional%20poverty%20measures%20exist%2C%20data%20limitations%20and%20subjectivity%20have%20hindered%20their%20robustness%2C%20making%20the%20headcount%20ratio%2C%20supplemented%20by%20metrics%20like%20the%20Human%20Development%20Index%20(HDI)%2C%20a%20reliable%20measure.%20Growth%20reduces%20poverty%20by%20lifting%20households%20above%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20but%20reductions%20become%20more%20complex%20over%20time%20as%20poverty%20ratios%20tend%20to%20be%20sticky.%20This%20trend%20is%20empirically%20validated%20by%20cross-country%20data%20and%20India's%20historical%20experience%2C%20with%20poverty%20reduction%20correlated%20with%20economic%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChanging%20Food%20Consumption%20Patterns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20we%20have%20the%20results%20of%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20HCES%202022-24%2C%20i.e.%2C%20for%20the%20year%202022-23.%20The%20second%20phase%20of%20HCES%202022-24%20fieldwork%20had%20also%20commenced%20on%2025%20August%202023%2C%20and%20by%20now%2C%20it%20would%20also%20have%20been%20concluded.%20Since%20the%20consumption%20data%20for%20the%20second%20phase%20will%20also%20be%20available%20soon%2C%20it%20will%20be%20possible%20to%20arrive%20at%20(a)%20the%20poverty%20ratios%20based%20on%20the%20existing%20poverty%20line%20and%20(b)%20formulate%20a%20new%20poverty%20line%20based%20on%20the%20new%20consumption%20patterns%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20understand%20peculiar%20trends%20in%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20HCES%202022-23.%20The%20recent%20working%20paper%20by%20Kapoor%20et%20al.%2C%20published%20by%20the%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20presents%20significant%20findings%20on%20India's%20changing%20food%20consumption%20patterns%2C%20with%20wide-reaching%20implications%20for%20agriculture%2C%20nutrition%2C%20health%2C%20and%20public%20welfare%20policies.%20The%20analysis%20of%20HCES%202022-23%20highlights%20the%20shift%20from%20cereal-based%20diets%20to%20more%20diverse%20food%20consumption%2C%20including%20an%20increase%20in%20milk%2C%20meat%2C%20fruits%2C%20and%20processed%20foods.%20This%20transformation%20directly%20affects%20food%20security%20and%20health%20outcomes%20across%20socio-economic%20classes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPer%20Capita%20Expenditure%20Has%20Increased%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20four%20key%20findings.%20First%2C%20there%20is%20a%20significant%20rise%20in%20per%20capita%20consumption%20expenditure.%20Rural%20households%20experienced%20a%20164%25%20increase%2C%20while%20urban%20households%20saw%20a%20146%25%20rise.%20States%20such%20as%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20exhibited%20substantial%20growth%20in%20consumption%20expenditures%2C%20with%20rural%20Sikkim%20leading%20at%20394%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20and%20most%20important%20trend%20is%20the%20declining%20share%20of%20food%20expenditure.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20since%20independence%2C%20average%20household%20spending%20on%20food%20has%20dropped%20below%2050%25%20of%20total%20expenditure.%20This%20trend%20suggests%20improved%20living%20standards%20and%20economic%20progress%2C%20as%20theorised%20by%20Engel's%20Law%2C%20which%20postulates%20that%20as%20incomes%20rise%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20income%20spent%20on%20food%20declines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThird%2C%20cereal%20consumption%20is%20declining.%20The%20fall%20was%20particularly%20stark%20among%20the%20bottom%2020%25%20of%20households%2C%20likely%20due%20to%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20government%20food%20security%20policies%20such%20as%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Anna%20Yojana%20(PMGKAY)%2C%20which%20provides%20free%20food%20grains%20to%20millions.%3Cbr%3E%5CnThis%20shift%20in%20consumption%20toward%20diverse%20foods%20-%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20dairy%2C%20and%20animal%20proteins%20-%20calls%20for%20a%20re-examination%20of%20India's%20agricultural%2C%20health%2C%20and%20nutrition%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Need%20For%20Diversifying%20Agriculture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20report's%20clearest%20policy%20implications%20is%20the%20need%20to%20reorient%20agricultural%20policies%20towards%20diet%20diversification.%20The%20continued%20focus%20on%20cereals%20through%20the%20Minimum%20Support%20Price%20(MSP)%20and%20procurement%20systems%20disproportionately%20benefits%20cereal%20producers%20while%20demand%20for%20cereals%20is%20declining.%20This%20mirrors%20the%20findings%20of%20Pingali%20and%20Sunder%20(2017)%2C%20who%20argue%20that%20cereal-centric%20policies%20in%20India%20are%20outdated%20and%20ignore%20the%20growing%20need%20for%20diversification%20in%20agricultural%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiversification%20towards%20horticulture%2C%20dairy%2C%20and%20livestock%20production%20offers%20a%20promising%20pathway%20for%20improving%20agricultural%20productivity%20and%20nutrition%20outcomes.%20This%20is%20also%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20government's%20efforts%20to%20prioritise%20investments%20in%20infrastructure%2C%20cold%20chains%2C%20storage%20facilities%2C%20and%20market%20access%20for%20perishable%20items%20like%20fruits%2C%20vegetables%2C%20milk%2C%20and%20meat%20to%20meet%20changing%20consumer%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20highlights%20the%20significant%20rise%20in%20consumption%20of%20packaged%20and%20processed%20foods%2C%20particularly%20among%20the%20wealthier%2020%25%20of%20households.%20NFHS%20V%20also%20flagged%20this%20issue%20as%20raising%20concerns%20about%20public%20health.%20There%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20literature%20showing%20a%20strong%20correlation%20between%20the%20rise%20of%20ultra-processed%20foods%20and%20the%20global%20epidemic%20of%20non-communicable%20diseases%20(NCDs)%20such%20as%20obesity%2C%20diabetes%2C%20and%20cardiovascular%20diseases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20should%20now%20focus%20on%20regulating%20the%20nutritional%20content%20of%20processed%20foods%20to%20mitigate%20their%20health%20impacts.%20Mandatory%20labelling%20and%20public%20health%20campaigns%20on%20the%20dangers%20of%20excessive%20processed%20food%20consumption%20should%20be%20considered%2C%20especially%20since%20these%20trends%20are%20more%20pronounced%20in%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%20And%20Children%20At%20Risk%20Of%20Anaemia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20report's%20analysis%20of%20anaemia%20and%20iron%20intake%20reveals%20a%20troubling%20finding.%20Despite%20various%20government%20initiatives%20to%20fortify%20food%20with%20iron%2C%20anaemia%20rates%20remain%20high%2C%20particularly%20among%20women%20and%20children.%20Again%2C%20this%20was%20also%20flagged%20by%20NFHS%20V.%20The%20study%2C%20however%2C%20confirms%20that%20dietary%20diversity%2C%20not%20just%20iron%20intake%2C%20is%20crucial%20in%20addressing%20anaemia%2C%20which%20aligns%20with%20findings%20from%20Ruel%20and%20Alderman%20(2013).%20Their%20research%20highlights%20the%20importance%20of%20dietary%20diversity%20in%20improving%20overall%20nutrition%20and%20health%20outcomes%2C%20particularly%20in%20reducing%20micronutrient%20deficiencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20limited%20impact%20of%20universal%20fortification%20programmes%20suggests%20that%20future%20policies%20should%20shift%20towards%20improving%20access%20to%20diverse%2C%20nutrient-rich%20foods.%20Promoting%20dietary%20diversity%20-%20by%20ensuring%20that%20poorer%20households%20can%20access%20iron-rich%20foods%20such%20as%20green%20leafy%20vegetables%2C%20eggs%2C%20meat%2C%20and%20pulses%20-%20could%20have%20a%20more%20meaningful%20impact%20on%20anaemia%20prevalence%20than%20cereal%20fortification%20alone.%20The%20findings%20also%20suggest%20a%20need%20for%20context-specific%20interventions%20that%20account%20for%20regional%20dietary%20patterns%20and%20nutritional%20deficits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20highlights%20the%20relationship%20between%20economic%20growth%2C%20dietary%20diversity%2C%20and%20health%20outcomes%2C%20drawing%20from%20the%20extensive%20body%20of%20research%20on%20how%20income%20growth%20can%20lead%20to%20better%20nutrition.%20As%20household%20incomes%20rise%2C%20the%20data%20suggests%20that%20diets%20become%20more%20diverse%2C%20shifting%20away%20from%20cereals%20to%20foods%20with%20higher%20nutritional%20value%2C%20such%20as%20dairy%2C%20eggs%2C%20meat%2C%20and%20fresh%20fruits.%3Cbr%3E%5CnAccording%20to%20Timmer%20(2005)%2C%20economic%20development%20typically%20drives%20this%20transition%2C%20and%20improving%20infrastructure%2C%20transportation%2C%20and%20storage%20will%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20ensuring%20that%20diverse%20food%20items%20are%20accessible%20year-round%2C%20even%20in%20remote%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeasuring%20Inflation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20critical%20policy%20implication%20of%20this%20report%20is%20its%20impact%20on%20measuring%20inflation.%20With%20significant%20changes%20in%20food%20consumption%20patterns%2C%20the%20composition%20of%20the%20Consumer%20Price%20Index%20(CPI)%20needs%20to%20be%20updated%20to%20reflect%20shifts%20in%20household%20spending%20accurately.%20The%20decline%20in%20cereal%20consumption%20and%20the%20rise%20in%20spending%20on%20fruits%2C%20dairy%2C%20and%20animal-based%20products%20indicate%20a%20need%20to%20revise%20the%20weightage%20assigned%20to%20these%20categories%20in%20the%20CPI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20toward%20dietary%20diversity%2C%20rising%20incomes%2C%20and%20declining%20cereal%20consumption%20signals%20progress%20and%20calls%20for%20nuanced%20policy%20interventions.%20As%20economic%20growth%20drives%20this%20transformation%2C%20ensuring%20equitable%20access%20to%20nutrient-rich%20foods%2C%20rebalancing%20agricultural%20incentives%2C%20and%20updating%20inflation%20measures%20will%20be%20vital%20to%20addressing%20emerging%20health%2C%20food%20security%2C%20and%20public%20welfare%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bibek%20Debroy%20is%20Chairman%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20and%20Aditya%20Sinha%20is%20OSD%2C%20Research%2C%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1726825080000%2C%22visual%22