20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eau%20pair%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20almost%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHutchinson's%20current%20employers%20are%20the%20fourth%20wealthy%20family%20she's%20worked%20for%20stateside%20since%20September%202015.%20She's%20parlayed%20those%20experiences%20into%20a%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40angel__0209%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20successful%20side%20hustle%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20helping%20other%20would-be%20au%20pairs%20follow%20in%20her%20footsteps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20difference%20between%20an%20au%20pair%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnanny-share-benefits-less-expensive-childcare-social-interaction-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enanny%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20in%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20role.%20%26quot%3BAn%20au%20pair%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20like%20a%20cousin%20who%20lives%20with%20you%20and%20is%20part%20of%20the%20family%20%E2%80%94%20when%20they%20go%20out%20for%20dinner%2C%20you%20all%20go%20out%20for%20dinner%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20the%20extra%20eyes%20for%20the%20parents.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHutchinson%20has%20had%20negative%20and%20positive%20experiences%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20families%2C%20she%20felt%20unwelcome%20and%20overworked%2C%20but%20in%20others%2C%20she's%20been%20whisked%20off%20on%20snowboarding%20trips%20and%20vacations%20in%20Puerto%20Rico.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220711039e-5cc2-478c-afd6-4a14ece3c8d4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20job%20is%20quite%20low-paying%2C%20but%20there%20are%20perks%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOverseas%20applicants%20will%20likely%20be%20recruited%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-us-student-visa-work-microsoft-green-card-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJ-1%20visa%3C%2Fa%3E%20rules.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20count%20as%20a%20job.%20It's%20more%20like%20a%20cultural%20exchange%20program%2C%20often%20below%20minimum%20wage.%20It%20is%20peanuts%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20au%20pairs%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20be%20required%20to%20work%20nights%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20but%20will%20typically%20work%2045%20hours%20per%20week%20and%20a%20maximum%20of%2010%20hours%20a%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoard%20and%20lodging%20are%20covered%2C%20but%20wages%20are%20considered%20pocket%20money%3A%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aupairusa.org%2Fau-pair-cost%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520minimum%2520weekly%2520stipend%2520for%2Cstipend%2520of%2520%2524225.00%2520per%2520week.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20State%20Department%20has%20set%20a%20current%20minimum%20of%20%24225.00%20per%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20more%20seasoned%20au%20pairs%2C%20she%20said%2C%20make%20%24300-350.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20earns%20more%20than%20this%20because%20she%20negotiated%20a%20higher%20than%20minimum%20wage.%20%26quot%3BAu%20pairs%20are%20allowed%20to%20negotiate%20for%20more%3B%20however%2C%20most%20families%20pay%20this%20because%20au%20pairs%20are%20afraid%20to%20speak%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eb5135dd-4d4c-4edd-a1e2-e2f8a28605cb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20application%20process%20is%20rigorous%20but%20straightforward%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHutchinson%20studied%20theology%20and%20planned%20to%20go%20into%20ministry%20full-time.%20%26quot%3BMy%20family%20felt%20I%20was%20wasting%20my%20life%20by%20coming%20to%20live%20with%20another%20family%2C%20but%20I%20was%20frustrated%20with%20life%20at%20that%20moment.%20I%20was%20in%20a%20relationship%20but%20wasn't%20sure%20if%20I%20wanted%20to%20get%20married%20yet.%20So%20I%20was%20like%2C%20OK%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20find%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHutchinson's%20interest%20in%20becoming%20an%20au%20pair%20was%20sparked%20by%20her%20college%20dean%2C%20who%20talked%20fondly%20of%20her%20experiences%20as%20an%20au%20pair%20in%20America%20two%20decades%20earlier.%20%26quot%3BShe%20still%20spoke%20with%20her%20family%2C%20who%20would%20visit%20her.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20filled%20out%20the%20forms%20and%20paid%20fees%20to%20one%20of%20the%20many%20agencies%20she%20found%20online%20%E2%80%94%20around%201300%20ZAR%2C%20or%20about%20%2470.%20She%20had%20to%20have%20a%20driver's%20license%20and%20a%20high%20school%20education%20and%20undergo%20medical%20checks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20accepted%2C%20she%20was%20asked%20to%20upload%20a%20profile%2C%20including%20a%20video%2C%20which%20interested%20families%20could%20browse.%20Typically%2C%20they%20would%20video%20chat%20with%20a%20potential%20au%20pair%20from%20afar%20before%20hiring%20one%20for%20a%2012-month%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22431f484e-69df-4fc8-91de-6300511c1208%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHutchinson%20was%20unhappy%20with%20her%20first%20two%20families%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHutchinson's%20first%20employers%20didn't%20ring%20alarm%20bells%20until%20she%20landed%20in%20America.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20getting%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20house%2C%20and%20when%20I%20was%20done%2C%20they%20told%20me%20to%20go%20unpack%20my%20stuff%20in%20my%20room.%20I%20closed%20the%20door%20and%20bawled%20my%20eyes%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20felt%20like%20something%20was%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20couple%20were%20wealthy%20Indian-Americans%20in%20New%20Jersey%3B%20the%20father%20was%20a%20pharmaceutical%20VP%2C%20and%20the%20mother%20a%20medical%20director.%20There%20were%20two%20children%2C%20aged%2013%20and%206%2C%20where%20the%20latter%20was%20Hutchinson's%20prime%20focus.%20%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20they%20were%20unprepared%20for%20me%20or%20had%20forgotten%20I%20was%20coming%20in%20the%20three%20months%20since%20we%20last%20spoke.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20issue%20was%20a%20misunderstanding%20of%20her%20role%2C%20stretching%20the%20definition%20of%20childcare.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20water%20the%20plants%20%E2%80%94%20because%20they%20were%20the%20kid's%20favorite.%20I%20had%20to%20dust%20the%20cupboard%20%E2%80%94%20because%20the%20kid's%20doll%20was%20on%20top%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20struggled%20to%20connect%20with%20the%20kids%2C%20as%20they%20would%20speak%20Bengali%20to%20their%20parents.%20She%20quickly%20asked%20for%20a%20rematch%20(au%20pair%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Espeak%20for%20resigning).%20%26quot%3BThey%20said%20you%20can't%20go%20because%20we've%20already%20had%20two%20girls%20leave%20before%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20later%2C%20Hutchinson's%20father%20died%2C%20and%20she%20was%20offered%20compassionate%20leave%20to%20return%20to%20South%20Africa%20for%20the%20funeral.%20Once%20home%2C%20she%20rematched%20there%2C%20returning%20three%20weeks%20later%20to%20a%20different%20family%2C%20but%20not%20a%20better%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20another%20New%20Jersey-based%20family%2C%20with%20two%20school-age%20kids%20of%205%20and%208%2C%20a%20mother%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20deputy%20principal%2C%20and%20a%20father%20who%20ran%20a%20tech%20business.%20The%20mom%20had%20described%20her%20kids%20to%20Hutchinson%20as%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20a%20lot%20of%20energy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20was%20more%20complicated%3A%20Her%20special%20needs%20kids%20were%20in%20therapy%20and%20rarely%20able%20to%20play%20with%20other%20au%20pairs'%20children%20at%20the%20playground.%20The%20daughter%20was%20particularly%20difficult%20for%20Hutchinson%20to%20care%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2243f3c48b-429a-4db1-b767-bc0a04acbab1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20third%20family%20was%20a%20better%20fit%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20January%202016%2C%20Hutchinson%20was%20primed%20to%20return%20to%20South%20Africa%2C%20but%20she%20tried%20to%20rematch%20one%20last%20time.%20This%20family%20proved%20life-changing.%20%26quot%3BI%20still%20visit%20them%20to%20this%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20Colorado-based%20couple%2C%20both%20anesthesiologists%2C%20had%20a%209-year-old%20daughter%20and%20a%203-year-old%20son.%20They%20lived%20in%20the%20mountains%20and%20drove%20a%20nine-seater%20Denali.%20%26quot%3BWe%20went%20on%20vacation%20a%20lot.%20They're%20a%20snowboarding%20family%2C%20so%20they%20taught%20me%2C%20and%20we%20went%20camping.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20never%20felt%20pressured%20to%20work%20late%20and%20could%20come%20and%20go%20as%20she%20pleased.%20Hutchinson%20felt%20very%20much%20at%20home%20in%20the%20Rockies.%20%26quot%3BThe%20people%20were%20so%20welcoming%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiggest-culture-shocks-after-moving-from-italy-to-colorado-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColorado%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20by%20far%20the%20best%20place%20I%20lived.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bcc44968-fb3f-4d6d-9063-520f63ed6167%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EShe%20went%20back%20to%20South%20Africa%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20a%20forever%20move%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%20stay%2C%20she%20went%20home.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20after%20spending%20time%20in%20South%20Africa%20looking%20after%20a%20boy%20for%20a%20German%20family%20in%20her%20neighborhood%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20come%20back%20to%20the%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20different%2C%20wealthy%20family%20spotted%20her%20video%20and%20asked%20if%20she'd%20consider%20coming%20to%20live%20with%20them%20in%20Maryland.%20The%20mother%20was%20a%20thoracic%20surgeon%2C%20and%20the%20father%20was%20a%20VP.%20They%20had%20one%20young%20child%2C%20barely%206%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moment%20she%20arrived%20in%20September%202019%2C%20Hutchinson%20felt%20at%20home.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20overprepared%2C%20trying%20to%20ensure%20I%20had%20the%20best%20time%20ever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20five%20years%20later%2C%20Hutchinson%20is%20so%