%20develop%20and%20implement%20context-appropriate%20irrigation%20systems%20based%20on%20these%20principles%2C%20certain%20steps%20have%20to%20be%20taken%2C%20argues%20Dr%20Chorol%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EConduct%20thorough%20site%20assessments%20to%20understand%20local%20topography%2C%20water%20sources%2C%20and%20soil%20conditions.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEngage%20with%20local%20communities%20to%20incorporate%20traditional%20knowledge%20and%20practices.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDesign%20main%20canals%20that%20follow%20natural%20contours%20and%20use%20local%20materials%20for%20construction.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EImplement%20a%20network%20of%20smaller%20distribution%20channels%20that%20can%20be%20easily%20managed%20by%20farmers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIncorporate%20simple%2C%20low-tech%20water%20control%20structures%20that%20can%20be%20operated%20and%20maintained%20locally.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPromote%20drought-resistant%20crops%20and%20water-efficient%20farming%20techniques%20suitable%20for%20the%20local%20climate.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEstablish%20community-based%20management%20systems%20for%20equitable%20water%20distribution%20and%20system%20maintenance.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20integrating%20customary%20rules%20and%20practices%2C%20like%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Esa-ka%3C%2Fem%3E%20ceremony%20before%20the%20first%20watering%20of%20the%20field%2C%20can%20increase%20community%20buy-in%20for%20water%20conservation%20efforts.%20The%20deep%20ecological%20knowledge%20of%20local%20farmers%2C%20such%20as%20understanding%20soil%20moisture%20(%3Cem%3Eser%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20optimal%20irrigation%20timing%2C%20can%20be%20tapped%20to%20improve%20irrigation%20efficiency.%20Respecting%20local%20spiritual%20connections%2C%20like%20the%20belief%20in%20water%20deities%20(%3Cem%3Elhu%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20can%20promote%20conservation%20ethics%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20%3Cem%3Es